<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFABAB0BFF2D8BFFFE67FBC1" pageId="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFABAB0BFF2D8BFFFE67FBC1" blockId="9.[173,660,988,1328]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFF2D8BFFFEDCFC17" bold="true" box="[197,301,988,1009]" pageId="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C719CFCFFABAB0BFE598BFFFDCBFC17" authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2014" box="[433,570,988,1009]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maracayensis">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFE598BFFFDCBFC17" box="[433,570,988,1009]" italics="true" pageId="9">maracayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
speciesgroup, only members of this species have the entire integument light brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFABAB0BFF2D8C0FFD7AFAF0" pageId="9" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFABAB0BFF2D8C0FFDF4FB1D" blockId="9.[173,660,988,1328]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFF2D8C0FFE81FBA7" bold="true" box="[197,368,1068,1089]" pageId="9">Description. Size</emphasis>
: Length 
<quantity id="4C894A9AFFABAB0BFE578C0FFDF9FBA7" box="[447,520,1068,1089]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="9" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
; width 2.0 mm. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFF458C64FF16FBBA" bold="true" box="[173,231,1095,1116]" pageId="9">Form</emphasis>
: As in 
<figureCitation id="134AFBFAFFABAB0BFEDC8C64FE8FFBBA" box="[308,382,1095,1116]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="21.[197,237,1489,1508]" captionTargetBox="[173,1193,194,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-75@21.[172,1193,192,1465]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs. 92–97. Pujoliclerus species, habitus. 92) P. helvinus; 93) P. maracayensis; 94) P. modestus; 95) P. bilineatus;" pageId="9">Fig. 94</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFE628C64FDF3FBBA" bold="true" box="[394,514,1095,1116]" pageId="9">Integument</emphasis>
: Light brown. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFF458C42FF13FB90" bold="true" box="[173,226,1121,1142]" pageId="9">Head</emphasis>
: Eyes not as wide as frons (12:15). 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFDAA8C42FD7DFB90" bold="true" box="[578,652,1121,1142]" pageId="9">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotum quadrate (41:41), lateral tubercle prominent (
<figureCitation id="134AFBFAFFABAB0BFF0E8CB5FEC1FB4D" box="[230,304,1174,1195]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="18.[175,215,1395,1414]" captionTargetBox="[151,1155,183,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-114@18.[151,1172,183,1383]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs. 48–61. Pujoliclerus species, pronota. 48) P. helvinus; 49) P. maracayensis; 50) P. modestus; 51) P. bilineatus; 52) P. calceatus; 53) P. corumba; 54) P. flavolimbatus; 55) P. ovatus; 56) P. wappesi; 57) P. amplus; 58) P. flavoapicalus; 59) P. gilvus; 60) P. hermani; 61) P. orellana." pageId="9">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
); epipleural fold gradually narrowed to elytral apex, asetiferous punctures prominent to elytral apex, interstitial spaces very arenose. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFF458CC5FEE1FB1D" bold="true" box="[173,272,1254,1275]" pageId="9">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Aedeagus not available.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFABAB0BFF2D8D22FD7AFAF0" blockId="9.[173,660,988,1328]" box="[197,651,1281,1302]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFF2D8D22FE9CFAF0" bold="true" box="[197,365,1281,1302]" pageId="9">Natural History.</emphasis>
No information is available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFABAB0BFF2D8D38FD63FAD6" box="[197,658,1307,1328]" pageId="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFABAB0BFF2D8D38FD63FAD6" blockId="9.[173,660,988,1328]" box="[197,658,1307,1328]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFF2D8D38FEB3FAD6" bold="true" box="[197,322,1307,1328]" pageId="9">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from 
<collectingCountry id="F366A7EFFFABAB0BFE1E8D38FDDCFAD6" box="[502,557,1307,1328]" name="Brazil" pageId="9">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="134AFBFAFFABAB0BFDD08D38FD77FAD6" box="[568,646,1307,1328]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="27.[197,229,1686,1705]" captionTargetBox="[173,659,1008,1663]" captionTargetId="figure-72@27.[172,659,1007,1663]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Fig. 125. Geographic distribution of six Pujoliclerus species." pageId="9">Fig. 125</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
